  "body": "Dynasty transition happens when the last two epochs were both justified. This issue implements dynasty transition logic for beacon chain node. A node should detect when last two epochs were both justified and perform the following operations:\r\n\r\n- Increase `crystallized_state.dynasty` by 1\r\n- Go through all queued_validators, in order from first to last. Any validators whose switch_dynasty is equal to or earlier than the new dynasty are immediately added to the end of active_validators \r\n- Go through all active_validators, and move any with either (i) balance equal to <= 50% of their initial balance, or (ii) switch_dynasty equal to or less than the new current dynasty, to exited_validators, moving up to a maximum of `(len(crystallized_state.active_validators) // 30) + 1` validators\r\n- Increment the current epoch\r\n- Set the current_checkpoint to the hash of the previous block\r\n- Reset the balance deltas, FFG voter bitfield\r\n",
